Package: pclmbayes
Type: Package
Title: Bayesian Density Estimation from Grouped Continuous Data via the
    Penalised Composite Link Model
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R: c(
    person("Chris", "K.",
           email = "christodoulosk@gmail.com",
           role = c("aut", "cre")),
    person("Philippe", "Lambert",
           role = c("ctb"),
           comment = "Author of the underlying method (Lambert & Eilers, 2009)"),
    person("Paul H. C.", "Eilers",
           role = c("ctb"),
           comment = "Author of the underlying method (Lambert & Eilers, 2009)"))
Description: Estimates a smooth latent continuous density from data
    that have been grouped (binned) into wide, possibly irregular or
    overlapping intervals. The log of the latent density is modelled on
    a fine grid using P-splines (B-spline basis with a difference
    penalty on the coefficients) and the wide-bin counts are linked to
    the latent density through a composite-link model with a multinomial
    likelihood. Both a frequentist penalised-scoring fit and a fully
    Bayesian fit (using a modified Langevin-Hastings sampler with an
    adaptive step size and a Gibbs step on the penalty parameter) are
    provided. Optional shape-constraint priors (unimodality,
    log-concavity, monotonicity) are supported. Implements the method
    of Lambert and Eilers (2009)
    <doi:10.1016/j.csda.2008.11.022>. British English is used in
    documentation.
